<section aria-label="Units">
  <div class="section-grid">
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-0/">
      <div class="card-title">Unit 0 — Scientific Practices & Class Foundations</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Three weeks. The lens you use for every other unit. OPVL, the AI Documentation Protocol, and the Source Dossier summative.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-1/">
      <div class="card-title">Unit 1 — Earth and Universe</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Five weeks. Habitability and systems. Earth + Mars + a student-chosen exoplanet, all evaluated against a student-built habitability framework, defended in a peer NASA Stakeholder Q&A.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-2/">
      <div class="card-title">Unit 2 — Surface Processes</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Nine blocks. Reading the Landscape. Students choose one of nine Chennai-area locations and write a Landscape Biography (past → present → 50-year projections) for a planning audience. Field Geologist AI partner introduced.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-3/">
      <div class="card-title">Unit 3 — Plate Tectonics & Natural Hazards</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Twelve blocks. Tectonic City Builder simulator. Two assessments: City Hazard Profile and Engineering Design Portfolio + Final Defense.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-4/">
      <div class="card-title">Unit 4 — Atmosphere & Climate</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Twelve blocks. Climate science + policy. Students learn the physics (greenhouse, carbon cycle, IPCC, models), then write a 4-page Chennai Climate Brief on one of 8 adaptation challenges for the Greater Chennai Corporation, defended in a peer Policy Panel. Climate Modeler + Policy Aide AI partners introduced.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-5/">
      <div class="card-title">Unit 5 — Hydrosphere</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Nine blocks. Water, stakeholders, and position. Students take a stakeholder perspective in one of 8 water-rights disputes (Cauvery anchor + Indus, Colorado, Nile, Mekong, Aral, Cooum, Bangalore), write a Position Paper from that perspective, and defend it in a multi-stakeholder Roundtable. The Hydrologist + Stakeholder Voice AI partners introduced. Matthew's trial unit — three pedagogical arms running concurrently.</div>
    </a>
    <a class="section-card" href="/units/unit-6/">
      <div class="card-title">Unit 6 — Biosphere & Land Use</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Ten blocks. The 15-minute neighborhood. Students redesign a Chennai area across 8 urban land uses, quantify the trade-offs (access, housing, green-blue, heat, flood, equity, mobility), and present at the school's environmental showcase to a real municipal audience. The Urban Planner + Equity & Resilience AI partners introduced.</div>
    </a>
    <div class="section-card stub">
      <div class="card-title">Unit 7 — Energy & Sustainability</div>
      <div class="card-desc">Coming soon. Energy mix design + public Op-Ed — the year's final unit.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
